abstract: Commissioner Pete Rozelle yesterday charged Al Davis, the managing general partner of the Oakland Raiders, with trying to intimidate National Football League owners through "distasteful publicity" as a way of forcing the league to accept the Raiders' effort to move to Los Angeles.

abstract: LOS ANGELES, Dec. 23 (AP)--The controversy involving the Los Angeles Rams and the alleged scalping of football tickets spread further today, with a newspaper report saying Al Davis had charged in a deposition that Carroll Rosenbloom, the late owner of the Rams, had asked him to take part in a scheme to scalp Super Bowl tickets.

abstract: Pete Rozelle said yesterday that he was dissatisfied with one aspect of the tie-breaking procedures used to qualify teams for the National Football League's postseason playoffs and that he was open to suggestions for improvements.

abstract: IRVING, Tex., Dec. 21--The Dallas Cowboys beat the Philadelphia Eagles by 35-27 today in a contest that set up the first round of the postseason playoffs for the National Football Conference.

abstract: WASHINGTON--Ronald Reagan's campaign pledge to balance the Federal budget without "altering or taking back necessary entitlements"--benefits to which individuals have a right in law--seems destined to be one of the first campaign promises broken.
